snippet.textDisplay: Laughable. U live ur life in ur way. Chinese live in our way. My mother is in 80s and lives in Shanghai. For 4 days she had no fresh vegetables. I am so glad she lives in Shanghai instead of Europe or US. Chinese value senior people‘s life.  U do not have to agree.
snippet.textOriginal: Laughable. U live ur life in ur way. Chinese live in our way. My mother is in 80s and lives in Shanghai. For 4 days she had no fresh vegetables. I am so glad she lives in Shanghai instead of Europe or US. Chinese value senior people‘s life.  U do not have to agree.

snippet.textDisplay:
How is locking them up without fresh vegetables better than giving the elderly freedom and respect?

I think you have a misconception on how we treat our elderly. In our country (Netherlands) they are the richest demographic and have the spare time to spend this.

They are also the most powerful because they are the biggest group and we have free elections, so they can use this benefit.

I can't think of a single aspect where they would be better off in China
